<body>
Reports references inside the following Persistence ORM annotations if they cannot be resolved within the configured datasource:<br/>
<ul>
  <li> Table</li>
  <li> Column</li>
  <li> [Any]To[Any]</li>
  <li> JoinColumn / JoinTable</li>
  <li> NamedQuery / NativeQuery</li>
  <li> Embeddable</li>
</ul><br/>

Suggests refreshing the datasource or assigning a different one.<br/>

<p><b>Example database table:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="sql">
  CREATE TABLE DATA_TABLE (
    ID INTEGER,
    DATA VARCHAR(100)
);
</code></pre><br/>

<p><b>Example JPA entity class:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="java">
  @Entity
  @Table(name = "UNKNOWN_TABLE") // unresolved reference
  public class JavaEntity {
    @Column(name = "ID") // cannot resolve columns in a table that's not defined
    Integer id;
  }
</code></pre><br/>

<!-- tooltip end -->
<p>
  <b>NOTE:</b> Datasource can be configured via `Assign datasource` action or the corresponding gutter icon for entity class
</p>
</body>
